{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-note-template-js","path":"/black pepper soup attempt one/","result":{"pageContext":{"id":"0a7e4b25-ec66-55e0-8963-7ed8ba94f6ad","html":"<h1>black pepper beef soup attempt #1</h1>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 102.7027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"soup in a dutch oven covered by a healthy layer of peppercorns\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/1c72d/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/a80bd/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 148w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/1c91a/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 295w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/1c72d/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 590w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/a8a14/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 885w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/fbd2c/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 1180w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/d3c45/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span>\nadapted <a href=\"https://www.andy-cooks.com/blogs/recipes/yukgaejang-spicy-korean-beef-soup\">andy cook's yukgaejang</a> but skipped the gochugaru/garlic/sesame oil and fernbrake, and added 1/4-1/2 cup black peppercorns.</p>\n<p>i tasted it and I think it needs an additional ingredient and accent flavor to round it out. Also add herbs next time.  filter the peppercorns after the broth is done.</p>\n<p>some suggested pairings i found for next time:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>garlic</li>\n<li>basil</li>\n<li>ginger</li>\n<li>parsley</li>\n<li>thyme</li>\n<li>peas</li>\n<li>scallions</li>\n<li>spinach</li>\n<li>vegetables</li>\n<li>radishes maybe too as garnish</li>\n</ul>"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}